<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="TI8" checkit-title="Improper integrals">
    <statement>
        <p>
             Determine which of the following integrals coverges and which diverges.  If an integral diverges, explain why.  If it converges, explain to which value it converges.
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li><m>\displaystyle\int_{ -1 }^{ 5 } \frac{1}{{\left(x + 1\right)}^{4}} dx.</m></li>
            <li><m>\displaystyle\int_{ 5 }^{ \infty } \frac{1}{{\left(x + 1\right)}^{4}} dx.</m></li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
       <ol>
            <li>
                <m>\displaystyle\int_{ -1 }^{ 5 } \frac{1}{{\left(x + 1\right)}^{4}} dx</m> diverges.               
            </li>            
           
            <li>
                <m>\displaystyle\int_{ 5 }^{ \infty } \frac{1}{{\left(x + 1\right)}^{4}} dx</m> converges to <m>\frac{1}{648}</m>.                
            </li>            
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
